1
00:00:21,855 --> 00:00:23,023
Hi, Mom.

2
00:00:32,532 --> 00:00:33,742
[Sunok exhales]

3
00:00:35,744 --> 00:00:37,162
Well, if you're calling me that...

4
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:41,542
...then I guess I really must be dying.

5
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:46,046
GANGWON SAEBAEK HOSPITAL

6
00:00:51,969 --> 00:00:53,387
The surgery went well.

7
00:00:54,388 --> 00:00:56,848
You're all right.
You'll be okay.

8
00:00:58,058 --> 00:00:59,726
You're not a very good liar.

9
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:03,605
Just like someone else I know.

10
00:01:04,439 --> 00:01:06,233
I'm looking into other hospitals.

11
00:01:07,401 --> 00:01:10,112
We'll transfer you,
redo the surgery,

12
00:01:10,195 --> 00:01:11,655
with the best doctor.

13
00:01:12,781 --> 00:01:14,032
Stop it.

14
00:01:16,493 --> 00:01:18,036
There's no point, really.

15
00:01:18,620 --> 00:01:20,372
It's been a miserable life.

16
00:01:23,083 --> 00:01:24,167
[exhales]

17
00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:25,460
It's time now.

18
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:27,713
[Sunok] You should go.

19
00:01:29,214 --> 00:01:32,092
So I can rest in peace.

20
00:01:34,011 --> 00:01:36,221
<i>Why does it matter if I'm here?</i>

21
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:41,059
Staying with me will only
make things harder for you.

22
00:01:41,143 --> 00:01:42,603
I know that.

23
00:01:44,187 --> 00:01:46,023
I really hated my life here.

24
00:01:47,649 --> 00:01:49,443
And I resented you a lot, too.

25
00:01:51,445 --> 00:01:52,446
[Heeju inhales]

26
00:01:52,988 --> 00:01:56,408
[Heeju] It hurt every time you called me
a luckless brat

27
00:01:56,491 --> 00:01:58,910
or told me nothing will ever work out.

28
00:02:00,203 --> 00:02:01,872
Just give up and live with it.

29
00:02:03,874 --> 00:02:05,709
Just hearing you say those things...

30
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:10,297
...made it impossible to even dream.

31
00:02:12,257 --> 00:02:13,508
But I realized...

32
00:02:14,343 --> 00:02:16,428
...that's just how you had
to live your life.

33
00:02:18,972 --> 00:02:21,808
[Heeju] And that's why I ran because
I didn't want to live like you.

34
00:02:23,352 --> 00:02:24,603
I thought that maybe...

35
00:02:26,563 --> 00:02:28,315
...if I just ran far enough...

36
00:02:29,858 --> 00:02:32,736
...I could find a way out of that long,
dark tunnel.

37
00:02:34,321 --> 00:02:35,947
<i>[Heeju inhales]</i>

38
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,825
<i>But no matter how far I ran...</i>

39
00:02:38,909 --> 00:02:41,244
<i>[Heeju inhales and exhales deeply]</i>

40
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:43,330
<i>...there was no end.</i>

41
00:02:45,457 --> 00:02:48,210
<i>That's when I realized I wasn't in</i>
<i>a tunnel at all.</i>

42
00:02:51,963 --> 00:02:53,590
I was in a mine shaft.

43
00:02:55,842 --> 00:02:57,552
[Heeju] And if I kept going...

44
00:02:59,805 --> 00:03:01,765
...there was only a dead end.

45
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:06,103
[inhales and exhales sharply]

46
00:03:06,186 --> 00:03:07,187
[sniffs]

47
00:03:07,938 --> 00:03:10,524
Then some man showed up
and offered me his hand.

48
00:03:11,483 --> 00:03:13,276
He helped me get out of there.

49
00:03:15,612 --> 00:03:17,572
Everything was so bright.

50
00:03:19,032 --> 00:03:22,119
[Heeju] I was blinded by him.
He was all I could see.

51
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:25,539
Funny, isn't it?

52
00:03:25,622 --> 00:03:27,416
I thought I was different.

53
00:03:27,916 --> 00:03:29,960
But I relied on a man
just like you.

54
00:03:31,044 --> 00:03:32,295
[inhales]

55
00:03:32,379 --> 00:03:34,005
All I ever wanted...

56
00:03:34,881 --> 00:03:37,259
...was for your life
to turn out differently.

57
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:42,848
[Heeju] <i>They say daughters</i>
<i>take after their mothers.</i>

58
00:03:43,432 --> 00:03:44,683
[Sunok] <i>Don't say that.</i>

59
00:03:46,184 --> 00:03:47,894
<i>That's exactly why...</i>

60
00:03:49,438 --> 00:03:51,773
<i>...I never wanted you</i>
<i>to call me Mom.</i>

61
00:04:02,742 --> 00:04:03,952
[inhales]

62
00:04:05,036 --> 00:04:06,913
Will you tell me what my father was like?

63
00:04:08,874 --> 00:04:10,041
[Sunok] Why?

64
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:11,960
You've never asked about him.

65
00:04:13,003 --> 00:04:14,212
[Heeju] I know.

66
00:04:15,839 --> 00:04:17,340
I guess I'm just curious...

67
00:04:18,175 --> 00:04:20,635
...now that I might never
have another chance to ask.

68
00:04:21,678 --> 00:04:23,847
He was a poor man.

69
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:26,057
[sniffles]

70
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:28,351
And you picked him?

71
00:04:29,227 --> 00:04:30,520
I'm surprised.

72
00:04:31,730 --> 00:04:32,814
I know.

73
00:04:36,026 --> 00:04:38,403
Out of all those men I was with...

74
00:04:40,197 --> 00:04:43,200
...he was the only one
I truly gave my heart to.

75
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:47,579
[Heeju] <i>What?</i>

76
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:49,581
<i>Was he your first love?</i>

77
00:04:50,624 --> 00:04:51,666
<i>[Sunok laughs]</i>

78
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:55,170
<i>I guess.</i>

79
00:04:57,380 --> 00:04:59,341
<i>He was so handsome.</i>

80
00:05:02,385 --> 00:05:04,221
One day when I was younger...

81
00:05:04,930 --> 00:05:07,140
...there was a fight at work.

82
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:09,684
[Sunok] <i>He showed up in his uniform.</i>

83
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:12,771
<i>He swept me into his arms</i>
<i>and saved me.</i>

84
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:15,982
He just seemed so cool.

85
00:05:18,527 --> 00:05:19,903
[Sunok] It felt like...

86
00:05:21,530 --> 00:05:25,367
...that uniform would protect me forever.

87
00:05:31,957 --> 00:05:33,250
[Sunok] <i>So...</i>

88
00:05:36,211 --> 00:05:38,171
...what happened with
that man you mentioned?

89
00:05:41,174 --> 00:05:42,467
It's over now.

90
00:05:43,593 --> 00:05:44,594
Why?

91
00:05:47,639 --> 00:05:50,851
[zipper unzipping]

92
00:05:51,518 --> 00:05:52,978
[Heeju exhales]

93
00:05:57,524 --> 00:05:58,733
It's because of this.

94
00:06:01,820 --> 00:06:03,280
[Sunok] <i>What?</i>

95
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:04,573
What is that?

96
00:06:05,115 --> 00:06:06,116
[Heeju] Mom.

97
00:06:06,616 --> 00:06:08,785
With something like this,

98
00:06:08,869 --> 00:06:12,581
you can do anything you want to do
and avoid anything you don't want.

99
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:16,167
That's probably why people will do
whatever they can to get it.

100
00:06:16,251 --> 00:06:17,544
[breathing shakily]

101
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:20,630
I did, too.

102
00:06:23,425 --> 00:06:26,553
I was afraid to face someone I loved
and was grateful for...

103
00:06:27,429 --> 00:06:29,222
[Heeju] ...because I really thought...

104
00:06:30,098 --> 00:06:31,683
...I thought he'd take it all from me.

105
00:06:34,185 --> 00:06:36,730
So I decided I'm going
to give him back half of it.

106
00:06:36,813 --> 00:06:38,481
It was his in the first place.

107
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:40,984
[Heeju] I know I'm selfish.

108
00:06:41,568 --> 00:06:43,695
But maybe by doing this
I will finally be able

109
00:06:43,778 --> 00:06:46,740
to find happiness in this life
just like I always wanted.

110
00:06:48,158 --> 00:06:49,326
I have to try.

111
00:06:50,076 --> 00:06:51,411
[Sunok] You...

112
00:06:53,496 --> 00:06:54,706
This is why.

113
00:06:54,789 --> 00:06:56,207
[inhales]

114
00:06:57,959 --> 00:07:00,420
This is why you've been acting so strange.

115
00:07:02,422 --> 00:07:04,341
Even after seeing me...

116
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:08,970
...you still don't know what happens
when greed takes over?

117
00:07:10,722 --> 00:07:14,976
[Sunok] Heeju, you never used
to be like this.

118
00:07:16,061 --> 00:07:18,480
I know that.
I know I've changed.

119
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:23,109
Is that really such a bad thing?

120
00:07:23,193 --> 00:07:27,197
[Heeju] If I'm nothing but bad luck
and I was never meant to have this

121
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:28,990
and I just give it up,

122
00:07:29,074 --> 00:07:31,117
what do you think's going
to happen to me then?

123
00:07:32,702 --> 00:07:38,041
I'll just live Kim Heeju's old life
and die Yeo Sunok's death.

124
00:07:39,417 --> 00:07:41,503
Is that the kind
of future you want for me?

125
00:07:43,588 --> 00:07:45,215
Heeju.

126
00:07:46,257 --> 00:07:47,342
Don't worry, Mom.

127
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:49,177
I'll be outta here soon.

128
00:07:49,761 --> 00:07:51,680
Just like you wanted, only...

129
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:54,432
...I want you to come with me, too.

130
00:07:54,933 --> 00:07:56,351
Where are you going to go?

131
00:07:58,812 --> 00:07:59,896
Far away.

132
00:08:01,231 --> 00:08:02,565
Somewhere very far.

133
00:08:02,649 --> 00:08:05,652
[wind rustling tree branches]

134
00:08:05,735 --> 00:08:07,779
[birds chirping]

135
00:08:07,862 --> 00:08:10,490
[Heeju] <i>To a small French village up on</i>
<i>a mountaintop...</i>

136
00:08:11,908 --> 00:08:14,035
<i>...past endless fields of lavender.</i>

137
00:08:14,119 --> 00:08:15,829
[church bell chimes]

138
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:17,622
[Heeju] <i>It never smells like coal mines.</i>

139
00:08:17,706 --> 00:08:20,208
<i>It only smells like lavender</i>
<i>and clean air.</i>

140
00:08:21,209 --> 00:08:23,545
<i>Everyone there is happy and smiling.</i>

141
00:08:24,587 --> 00:08:27,966
<i>You and I can be like that, too,</i>
<i>if we go.</i>

142
00:08:30,552 --> 00:08:31,636
[Sunok] <i>Do you mean it?</i>

143
00:08:34,222 --> 00:08:35,807
You're gonna take me with you?

144
00:08:38,810 --> 00:08:39,936
Mm-hmm.

145
00:08:42,063 --> 00:08:43,106
[Sunok] Okay.

146
00:08:44,899 --> 00:08:46,276
And if I die...

147
00:08:48,236 --> 00:08:50,989
...you can still go and scatter my ashes.

148
00:08:57,495 --> 00:08:59,039
[sniffles]

149
00:09:16,806 --> 00:09:19,809
[♪ sad piano music]

150
00:09:53,551 --> 00:09:56,554
[♪ music continues]

151
00:09:59,349 --> 00:10:00,975
EPISODE 8
CHOICE

152
00:10:01,059 --> 00:10:02,977
[Woogy] My father gave this
to me before he passed away.

153
00:10:03,061 --> 00:10:04,062
[Shop Keeper] Oh, really?

154
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:07,065
Heh, still, who would
have thought the price

155
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:08,775
of gold would get this high, right?

156
00:10:08,858 --> 00:10:12,237
So these gold bars,
your father left them to you?

157
00:10:14,572 --> 00:10:16,866
Yeah. Well, he only gave me two.

158
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:21,246
And about two weeks ago you came in to,
uh, sell the other gold bar?

159
00:10:21,663 --> 00:10:24,332
Your name is Kim Mincheol,
isn't it, sir?

160
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:26,167
That was me, yeah.

161
00:10:26,251 --> 00:10:27,585
Please wait here a sec.

162
00:10:31,422 --> 00:10:32,423
[inhales]

163
00:10:32,507 --> 00:10:33,508
[clicks tongue]

164
00:10:36,970 --> 00:10:37,971
Everything in order?

165
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:39,055
- Yeah, it looks good.
- Good.

166
00:10:40,098 --> 00:10:42,100
Well, I'll see you again.

167
00:10:42,183 --> 00:10:43,351
- [laughs]
- Yeah.

168
00:10:43,977 --> 00:10:45,270
- Thank you very much.
- Sure.

169
00:10:45,353 --> 00:10:46,729
- Thank you, sir.
- Yeah.

170
00:10:49,607 --> 00:10:50,608
[door opens]

171
00:10:58,199 --> 00:10:59,325
[phone chimes]

172
00:10:59,534 --> 00:11:00,577
[phone trilling]

173
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:02,370
Hello, President Ko.

174
00:11:02,453 --> 00:11:04,873
I'm calling from Lucky Jewelry
in Daejeong.

175
00:11:04,956 --> 00:11:07,208
[car engine rumbling]

176
00:11:07,292 --> 00:11:10,295
[emergency sirens passing]

177
00:11:26,436 --> 00:11:28,771
[car engine turns over]

178
00:11:28,855 --> 00:11:30,732
[car engine starts]

179
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:45,705
[tires squeal]

180
00:11:51,502 --> 00:11:54,505
[engine revving]

181
00:12:01,971 --> 00:12:04,724
Where on Earth are you headed now?

182
00:12:10,271 --> 00:12:13,107
[engine revving]

183
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:16,903
[tires squealing]

184
00:12:33,628 --> 00:12:36,631
[car creaking]

185
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:42,720
[inhales deeply]

186
00:13:01,948 --> 00:13:04,951
[engine revving]

187
00:13:38,026 --> 00:13:40,570
[engine rumbling]

188
00:14:13,853 --> 00:14:15,563
Ah, shit.

189
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:21,694
[engine revving]

190
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:42,757
[breathing heavily]

191
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:45,009
[tires squealing]

192
00:14:55,353 --> 00:14:58,356
[cell phone vibrating]

193
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:03,861
Hello, sir?

194
00:15:03,945 --> 00:15:05,363
[Moonsu] <i>Where the hell are you right now?</i>

195
00:15:05,446 --> 00:15:07,824
Ju Haran's ID card, did you take it?

196
00:15:10,451 --> 00:15:12,203
What? Who?

197
00:15:12,954 --> 00:15:16,374
It's fucking chaos.
Ko has everyone looking for you.

198
00:15:16,457 --> 00:15:18,626
[Moonsu] <i>Get your ass back here</i>
<i>before things get out of hand.</i>

199
00:15:19,168 --> 00:15:21,629
Uh, I'm not sure what
you're talking about.

200
00:15:22,755 --> 00:15:24,757
And also, sir, I quit already.

201
00:15:25,883 --> 00:15:26,884
[Moonsu] <i>Woogy.</i>

202
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:29,512
<i>I'm warning you.</i>

203
00:15:30,388 --> 00:15:31,722
Uh, sir, but--
[phone disconnects]

204
00:15:32,348 --> 00:15:34,308
Ah, shit.

205
00:15:34,684 --> 00:15:36,394
Fuck, I knew this would happen.

206
00:15:36,477 --> 00:15:38,229
Shit, shit, shit, shit.

207
00:15:38,312 --> 00:15:39,772
[breathing heavily]

208
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:44,569
[breathing heavily]

209
00:15:44,652 --> 00:15:46,904
I'm fucked.
I'm fucked.

210
00:15:46,988 --> 00:15:48,906
Oh, shit, I'm so fucked.

211
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:51,033
[Woogy] How'd they know?

212
00:15:51,117 --> 00:15:54,120
[panicked breathing]

213
00:15:54,203 --> 00:15:55,621
Damn, this is crazy.

214
00:15:55,705 --> 00:15:58,291
[heavy breathing]

215
00:16:06,215 --> 00:16:07,383
Okay, okay.

216
00:16:07,466 --> 00:16:09,886
This'll be more than enough. Yeah?

217
00:16:11,721 --> 00:16:13,472
What else can I do?

218
00:16:13,556 --> 00:16:15,266
Gotta save my own ass first.

219
00:16:15,349 --> 00:16:16,809
[panting]

220
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:21,606
Right.

221
00:16:22,064 --> 00:16:23,316
I don't have a choice.

222
00:16:25,276 --> 00:16:27,820
Heeju, I'm sorry.

223
00:16:28,571 --> 00:16:29,906
I'm sorry.

224
00:16:29,989 --> 00:16:31,824
[car engine turns over]
[Woogy] Fuck, I don't know!

225
00:16:39,707 --> 00:16:42,710
[tires squealing]

226
00:16:48,674 --> 00:16:50,718
[car horn honking]

227
00:16:53,763 --> 00:16:54,764
[horn blares]

228
00:16:56,349 --> 00:16:57,475
Stop the car!

229
00:16:59,143 --> 00:17:00,937
[Jinman] Kim Heeju!

230
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,772
Stop the car and pull over!

231
00:17:03,314 --> 00:17:04,357
[exhales]

232
00:17:05,942 --> 00:17:08,569
[Jinman] Kim Heeju!
Stop! I need to talk to you!

233
00:17:09,362 --> 00:17:10,488
I just need a minute!

234
00:17:10,571 --> 00:17:12,573
Please, just pull over!

235
00:17:13,532 --> 00:17:14,909
[tires squealing]

236
00:17:16,077 --> 00:17:17,078
[gasps]

237
00:17:17,662 --> 00:17:18,996
[tires squealing]

238
00:17:19,747 --> 00:17:20,748
[clanging]

239
00:17:23,042 --> 00:17:25,002
[erratic breathing]

240
00:17:32,718 --> 00:17:34,178
Ah, shit.

241
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:38,724
[breathing heavily]

242
00:17:39,642 --> 00:17:41,143
[Jinman] Ms. Kim Heeju!

243
00:17:41,227 --> 00:17:42,603
[Jinman yanking door handle]

244
00:17:42,687 --> 00:17:46,440
Please step out of the car, yeah?
Don't you remember me?

245
00:17:46,524 --> 00:17:49,068
I'm a detective, Kim Jinman.
Don't you remember?

246
00:17:49,151 --> 00:17:50,778
I'm trying to help you!
You're in serious danger!

247
00:17:50,861 --> 00:17:51,862
Come on, step out!

248
00:17:52,363 --> 00:17:53,823
[Jinman] I'm not gonna hurt you!

249
00:17:56,617 --> 00:17:57,702
[exhales]

250
00:17:59,036 --> 00:18:02,873
[Jinman] Finally.
Okay, do you have a plan?

251
00:18:02,957 --> 00:18:04,292
You're in serious trouble.
You know that.

252
00:18:04,959 --> 00:18:05,960
Right?

253
00:18:06,961 --> 00:18:08,254
[Jinman] Where are the gold bars?

254
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:10,965
Are they in the car? Here?

255
00:18:11,048 --> 00:18:11,924
[car door opens]

256
00:18:13,217 --> 00:18:14,844
[exhales]

257
00:18:16,429 --> 00:18:18,681
[grunts]

258
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:28,441
[exhales]

259
00:18:29,734 --> 00:18:30,901
[Jinman] The gold bars, where were you--

260
00:18:30,985 --> 00:18:32,236
[Heeju gasps]

261
00:18:37,742 --> 00:18:38,951
Is that a real gun?

262
00:18:39,035 --> 00:18:41,120
[Jinman] Is it?
Have you ever even fired it?

263
00:18:41,746 --> 00:18:42,913
Come on. Give it here.

264
00:18:42,997 --> 00:18:44,665
[gun cocks]

265
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:46,792
[Heeju] Close the trunk right now.

266
00:18:48,085 --> 00:18:49,337
The trunk! Close it!

267
00:18:51,213 --> 00:18:54,216
[exhales]

268
00:18:59,722 --> 00:19:00,723
[Jinman] Kim Heeju.

269
00:19:00,806 --> 00:19:03,851
Listen, do you realize how serious
this situation is?

270
00:19:03,934 --> 00:19:07,063
Do you have any idea who you're dealing
with right now? Huh?

271
00:19:07,855 --> 00:19:09,774
[Jinman] The situation
is incredibly dangerous.

272
00:19:10,399 --> 00:19:12,401
The Geumseong guys.
Yes Money.

273
00:19:12,943 --> 00:19:14,862
It's only a matter
of time before they track you down.

274
00:19:14,945 --> 00:19:16,238
And once they do, they'll kill you!

275
00:19:16,322 --> 00:19:17,865
- [Jinman] Do you get that?
- Of course I do.

276
00:19:18,491 --> 00:19:22,036
Do you? Really?
Why do this, huh?

277
00:19:22,620 --> 00:19:24,789
[Jinman] Those gold bars
don't belong to you!

278
00:19:24,872 --> 00:19:26,374
They belong to Chairman Ahn!

279
00:19:26,832 --> 00:19:28,876
You can live if you return the gold!

280
00:19:29,460 --> 00:19:30,961
[Jinman] If you're too scared
to give it back,

281
00:19:31,045 --> 00:19:32,171
I'll do it for you.

282
00:19:32,588 --> 00:19:34,048
Then you can leave the country!

283
00:19:34,131 --> 00:19:36,467
I'll help you get a passport
and anything else you need!

284
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:37,843
[Heeju] Don't lie to me.

285
00:19:37,927 --> 00:19:40,721
What did Chairman Ahn promise you
for handing me over?

286
00:19:40,805 --> 00:19:43,140
Ah, you don't understand
a word I'm saying.

287
00:19:43,224 --> 00:19:44,392
[Heeju] Go!

288
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:46,602
Just get outta here, please!

289
00:19:46,686 --> 00:19:48,312
If I was going to,

290
00:19:48,396 --> 00:19:50,773
I would have given the gold back
a long time ago!

291
00:19:51,273 --> 00:19:52,900
[Jinman] The gold bars
have completely blinded you

292
00:19:52,983 --> 00:19:54,110
and now you're not thinking straight!

293
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:55,903
[Jinman] You've completely lost your mind!

294
00:19:56,487 --> 00:19:57,697
Just take a breath, okay?

295
00:19:57,780 --> 00:19:59,573
Let's try and be realistic here.

296
00:20:00,950 --> 00:20:03,160
You can't turn all the bars into cash.

297
00:20:03,244 --> 00:20:04,495
[Jinman] And even if you do,

298
00:20:04,578 --> 00:20:06,956
you realize that's over
100 billion won, right?

299
00:20:07,039 --> 00:20:09,166
How are you gonna spend all
that money before you die?

300
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:10,418
Huh?

301
00:20:10,918 --> 00:20:12,712
[Jinman] If I return the gold
to Chairman Ahn,

302
00:20:12,795 --> 00:20:14,004
he promised to pay me!

303
00:20:14,547 --> 00:20:16,215
And I'll give all of it to you.

304
00:20:17,466 --> 00:20:19,009
[Jinman] Then you get to live!

305
00:20:19,802 --> 00:20:21,554
You can go somewhere far away!

306
00:20:23,723 --> 00:20:24,807
Like France, huh?

307
00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:26,684
[Jinman] Take your mom
and go to France!

308
00:20:27,393 --> 00:20:29,270
Sound like a plan? Yeah?

309
00:20:29,353 --> 00:20:30,938
[Jinman] Give me the gun.

310
00:20:31,021 --> 00:20:31,897
[gunshot]

311
00:20:34,024 --> 00:20:35,109
Don't you dare move!

312
00:20:38,696 --> 00:20:40,197
Don't follow me.

313
00:20:40,614 --> 00:20:42,199
[Heeju] Don't go looking for me.

314
00:20:42,283 --> 00:20:43,743
And you'd better leave my aunt alone, too!

315
00:20:44,285 --> 00:20:45,494
[car door opens]

316
00:20:46,662 --> 00:20:47,955
[car engine turns over]

317
00:20:48,038 --> 00:20:49,206
Hey, Kim Heeju!

318
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:52,334
[clangs]

319
00:20:55,004 --> 00:20:56,589
[distant tires squealing]

320
00:20:59,425 --> 00:21:02,428
[car engine revving]

321
00:21:06,974 --> 00:21:08,267
[exhales]

322
00:21:12,021 --> 00:21:14,565
[cell phone vibrates]

323
00:21:14,648 --> 00:21:17,401
HEEJU

324
00:21:17,485 --> 00:21:19,028
Ah, dammit, seriously?

325
00:21:30,706 --> 00:21:33,709
[cell phone vibrates]

326
00:21:37,797 --> 00:21:39,298
HEEJU

327
00:21:39,799 --> 00:21:41,383
[clears throat]

328
00:21:41,467 --> 00:21:42,635
Hey, Heeju.

329
00:21:43,010 --> 00:21:45,012
[Heeju] <i>Detective Kim tailed me.</i>

330
00:21:45,095 --> 00:21:46,889
<i>He just pulled me over.</i>

331
00:21:46,972 --> 00:21:49,517
And he saw the gold bars in my trunk, too.

332
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:50,601
[Woogy] <i>What?</i>

333
00:21:50,684 --> 00:21:52,144
How did he know to follow you?

334
00:21:52,728 --> 00:21:54,605
[Heeju] <i>I think he was staking out</i>
<i>the hospital.</i>

335
00:21:54,688 --> 00:21:56,524
He had to be listening in.

336
00:21:57,650 --> 00:22:00,236
Somehow he knew everything I said
to my aunt there.

337
00:22:00,319 --> 00:22:01,779
[Woogy] <i>Wait. So then...</i>

338
00:22:02,947 --> 00:22:06,575
...he has to know you're really Kim Heeju
and not Ju Haran.

339
00:22:08,077 --> 00:22:10,079
[Woogy] <i>What about now?</i>
<i>Is he still tailing you?</i>

340
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:11,831
Uh, no. I'm okay.

341
00:22:12,414 --> 00:22:14,416
I threatened him with the gun and ran.

342
00:22:15,584 --> 00:22:17,002
Okay, good work.

343
00:22:17,086 --> 00:22:19,630
So anyway, now you better just
find somewhere to hide.

344
00:22:19,713 --> 00:22:20,714
And then...

345
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:23,384
...well, I'll figure out what's going on
and call you.

346
00:22:23,467 --> 00:22:24,468
[Heeju] <i>No.</i>

347
00:22:24,969 --> 00:22:27,847
I don't have time for that.
Where are you now?

348
00:22:27,930 --> 00:22:29,890
[Heeju] <i>Are you still at</i>
<i>the jewelry store?</i>

349
00:22:30,516 --> 00:22:31,851
<i>Did you get the cash yet?</i>

350
00:22:31,934 --> 00:22:34,103
Uh, yeah.

351
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:36,230
The jewelry store.

352
00:22:36,814 --> 00:22:38,148
I got the cash already.

353
00:22:39,108 --> 00:22:40,693
I'm gonna head that way now.

354
00:22:41,569 --> 00:22:42,778
I'll meet you there.

355
00:22:42,862 --> 00:22:44,113
[cell phone disconnects]

356
00:22:52,079 --> 00:22:53,455
Ah!

357
00:22:56,292 --> 00:22:57,585
[exhales]

358
00:22:57,668 --> 00:22:58,878
Dammit.

359
00:23:00,087 --> 00:23:01,714
[exhales]

360
00:23:01,797 --> 00:23:03,757
[Woogy] Okay, let's just run.

361
00:23:04,717 --> 00:23:05,968
All right.

362
00:23:06,051 --> 00:23:07,887
Fuck it. Whatever.

363
00:23:09,221 --> 00:23:10,764
Yeah, fuck it.
I don't care.

364
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:13,976
Ah, fuck.

365
00:23:14,059 --> 00:23:17,062
[tires squealing]
[car horns honking]

366
00:23:23,944 --> 00:23:25,029
[cell phone trilling]

367
00:23:25,112 --> 00:23:27,031
Hey, I'm almost there now.
What about you?

368
00:23:28,741 --> 00:23:29,992
[Heeju] <i>Are you there yet?</i>

369
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:31,368
Yeah, I'm here already.

370
00:23:31,452 --> 00:23:33,370
[Heeju] <i>You are?</i>
<i>I don't see you.</i>

371
00:23:34,246 --> 00:23:35,956
[Woogy] Do you see me waving
at the end of the alley?

372
00:23:38,751 --> 00:23:41,921
Oh. Yeah, I see you.

373
00:23:42,588 --> 00:23:43,589
Is that your car?

374
00:23:44,298 --> 00:23:45,925
Here, over here.
You can park--

375
00:23:50,554 --> 00:23:51,931
Uh, hey, Heeju.

376
00:23:52,014 --> 00:23:53,849
I think the guys are here.
Open the window. The window.

377
00:23:53,933 --> 00:23:55,225
Hurry. Open it. The window.

378
00:23:56,644 --> 00:23:58,354
Hey, isn't that Woogy?

379
00:23:59,813 --> 00:24:01,231
The window. Just open it.

380
00:24:01,690 --> 00:24:02,691
The window?

381
00:24:07,196 --> 00:24:08,322
- [Moonsu] Get him!
- [Woogy] Heeju!

382
00:24:08,405 --> 00:24:11,033
In my car! I got the gold bars
and the cash.

383
00:24:11,116 --> 00:24:12,451
[Woogy] <i>Go get 'em!</i>

384
00:24:12,534 --> 00:24:13,869
And then go hide somewhere! Hurry!

385
00:24:13,953 --> 00:24:15,079
- [Heeju] <i>Hello?</i>
- [Moonsu] Hey!

386
00:24:15,162 --> 00:24:16,830
[Woogy] Shit!
[breathing heavily]

387
00:24:16,914 --> 00:24:18,040
[Moonsu] Woogy!

388
00:24:19,041 --> 00:24:21,001
Woogy? You there?

389
00:24:25,965 --> 00:24:26,966
[Moonsu] Ah!

390
00:24:27,049 --> 00:24:29,385
[crowd shouting]

391
00:24:29,468 --> 00:24:31,971
[Moonsu] Son of a bitch!
Woogy!

392
00:24:33,597 --> 00:24:36,600
[Woogy breathing heavily]

393
00:24:37,601 --> 00:24:40,187
[Moonsu] Hey! Stop!

394
00:24:42,272 --> 00:24:44,108
- [Moonsu] Guys, split up!
- This way.

395
00:24:44,191 --> 00:24:45,234
[Henchman B] Come on!

396
00:24:46,026 --> 00:24:48,237
[Moonsu] Hey! You motherfucker!

397
00:24:48,320 --> 00:24:50,948
[Woogy breathing erratically]

398
00:24:52,783 --> 00:24:54,159
[all groaning]

399
00:24:54,827 --> 00:24:57,454
[Moonsu] What the fuck?
Go, go, go, go, go, go!

400
00:25:01,041 --> 00:25:02,042
[Moonsu] Get him!

401
00:25:02,126 --> 00:25:03,794
[Woogy breathing heavily]

402
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:09,091
[Woogy groaning]

403
00:25:09,174 --> 00:25:10,175
Come on, man.
We're like brothers.

404
00:25:10,259 --> 00:25:12,386
- Let's go, Woogy.
- [Woogy] Can't we talk it out?

405
00:25:12,469 --> 00:25:14,722
Stay back!
I said stay back, for fuck's sake!

406
00:25:16,390 --> 00:25:17,641
[Woogy] Don't come any closer.

407
00:25:17,725 --> 00:25:19,560
Ah, fuck this shit!

408
00:25:19,643 --> 00:25:20,728
[grunts]

409
00:25:20,811 --> 00:25:22,229
Shit, shit!

410
00:25:22,312 --> 00:25:23,605
[shouts]

411
00:25:24,732 --> 00:25:26,442
Shit, shit.

412
00:25:26,525 --> 00:25:28,152
- [groaning]
- [Moonsu] Ah, fuck!

413
00:25:28,235 --> 00:25:29,570
He went that way!
Come on, let's go!

414
00:25:30,863 --> 00:25:32,781
[breathing heavily]

415
00:25:32,865 --> 00:25:34,158
Oh, shit.

416
00:25:41,540 --> 00:25:44,001
Ah, fuck's sake.

417
00:25:44,084 --> 00:25:46,295
[labored breathing]

418
00:25:46,378 --> 00:25:47,755
Ah, shit.

419
00:25:50,549 --> 00:25:52,051
[door creaks]

420
00:25:52,593 --> 00:25:53,635
[grunts]

421
00:25:53,719 --> 00:25:55,345
[door locking]

422
00:25:55,721 --> 00:25:57,931
[groaning]

423
00:26:05,147 --> 00:26:06,774
[banging on door]

424
00:26:06,857 --> 00:26:08,275
[Moonsu] Woogy, open up!

425
00:26:09,777 --> 00:26:10,944
[Moonsu] I'm gonna break it down!

426
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:12,654
You hear me?

427
00:26:12,738 --> 00:26:13,864
[groans]

428
00:26:13,947 --> 00:26:15,157
[banging on door]

429
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:17,117
[Moonsu] Woogy!

430
00:26:24,416 --> 00:26:27,628
[cell phone vibrates]

431
00:26:27,711 --> 00:26:28,837
Woogy, hey.

432
00:26:29,213 --> 00:26:31,131
[Woogy breathing heavily]
[Woogy] <i>Heeju.</i>

433
00:26:31,799 --> 00:26:33,300
<i>[panting]</i>

434
00:26:33,383 --> 00:26:35,427
<i>What are you gonna do with that money?</i>

435
00:26:35,511 --> 00:26:37,429
What are you talking about?

436
00:26:37,513 --> 00:26:39,014
Tell me where you are, please.

437
00:26:40,099 --> 00:26:42,101
I've seen it happen over and over.

438
00:26:42,768 --> 00:26:43,894
[Moonsu] <i>Hey, Woogy!</i>

439
00:26:44,478 --> 00:26:47,356
Stupid people who got greedy
and ruined their lives.

440
00:26:47,856 --> 00:26:49,608
My father was one of those guys.

441
00:26:49,691 --> 00:26:52,694
[Moonsu] <i>Open the door while</i>
<i>I'm asking nicely. 'Kay?</i>

442
00:26:53,237 --> 00:26:55,489
And fuck me.
I guess I got greedy, too.

443
00:26:57,533 --> 00:26:59,618
[Woogy] <i>I didn't even get</i>
<i>to spend all the money.</i>

444
00:27:00,577 --> 00:27:02,246
Just tell me where you are right now.

445
00:27:02,913 --> 00:27:04,456
Did you get away from those guys?

446
00:27:05,541 --> 00:27:07,126
[Moonsu] Hey, motherfucker!

447
00:27:07,209 --> 00:27:08,794
Just open the door!

448
00:27:08,877 --> 00:27:10,212
- Heeju.
- [Moonsu] Huh?

449
00:27:11,713 --> 00:27:12,840
Open up!

450
00:27:14,591 --> 00:27:16,260
I won't last long at the farm, okay?

451
00:27:16,343 --> 00:27:18,428
- [Moonsu] You son of a bitch!
- I'll give up your name.

452
00:27:19,888 --> 00:27:24,184
[Woogy] <i>So as soon as we hang up,</i>
<i>you need to run as far as you can.</i>

453
00:27:25,060 --> 00:27:26,353
You can take all the gold.

454
00:27:26,645 --> 00:27:28,272
- [Moonsu] Break the door down.
- You'll find it in the trunk

455
00:27:28,355 --> 00:27:29,815
with the cash.
All of it is there.

456
00:27:29,898 --> 00:27:30,983
[Moonsu] Harder, you idiot!

457
00:27:31,066 --> 00:27:33,151
Take everything.
Take it and run.

458
00:27:33,235 --> 00:27:35,153
- [Woogy] <i>Got it?</i>
- Hey, you just--

459
00:27:35,237 --> 00:27:38,073
just make it as long as you can.
I'll--I'll be there right away.

460
00:27:38,657 --> 00:27:40,284
[Woogy]<i> You know</i>
<i>what this reminds me of?</i>

461
00:27:41,702 --> 00:27:43,245
<i>When we used to play freeze tag.</i>

462
00:27:44,079 --> 00:27:45,914
[bangs on door]
[Moonsu groans]

463
00:27:45,998 --> 00:27:48,083
I got tagged in the mining town
and had to freeze.

464
00:27:48,166 --> 00:27:49,293
[Moonsu] What are you doing?

465
00:27:49,793 --> 00:27:51,169
[Moonsu] Try lifting it.

466
00:27:51,628 --> 00:27:53,672
I was so scared until you tagged me.

467
00:27:53,755 --> 00:27:54,798
[Moonsu] Break the whole thing down!

468
00:27:54,882 --> 00:27:56,216
[door bangs]

469
00:27:56,300 --> 00:27:57,676
You really forgot all that?

470
00:27:57,759 --> 00:27:58,886
[door clanging]

471
00:27:59,511 --> 00:28:00,637
[exhales]

472
00:28:00,721 --> 00:28:01,889
- Woogy--
- [Woogy] <i>I gotta go.</i>

473
00:28:01,972 --> 00:28:03,765
- [Moonsu] <i>Open it, fucker!</i>
- Wait a minute.

474
00:28:03,849 --> 00:28:05,183
- Woogy? Hey!
- [Moonsu] <i>The fuck are you doing?</i>

475
00:28:05,726 --> 00:28:07,185
[breathing heavily]
[phone disconnects]

476
00:28:07,269 --> 00:28:10,272
[grunting]
[clanging]

477
00:28:11,356 --> 00:28:14,359
[all breathing heavily]

478
00:28:20,282 --> 00:28:21,283
[Moonsu] Woogy.

479
00:28:21,950 --> 00:28:22,993
Let's go.

480
00:28:25,954 --> 00:28:27,873
[exhales]

481
00:28:27,956 --> 00:28:29,499
Oh, what do I do?

482
00:28:31,460 --> 00:28:33,962
[car engine turns over]

483
00:28:36,715 --> 00:28:38,258
[exhales]

484
00:28:45,223 --> 00:28:46,224
The gold bars are in the trunk.

485
00:28:47,559 --> 00:28:48,602
[Dokyung] Heeju.

486
00:28:50,312 --> 00:28:53,023
I'll sell the gold bars
and I'll come right back.

487
00:28:53,774 --> 00:28:54,775
[grunts]

488
00:28:55,359 --> 00:28:56,401
Don't bother.

489
00:28:57,110 --> 00:28:59,279
This will be the last time
we see each other.

490
00:29:00,113 --> 00:29:01,865
[Dokyung] You still have
Ju Haran's account, right?

491
00:29:02,616 --> 00:29:04,242
Once I get the cash for the gold,

492
00:29:04,326 --> 00:29:06,244
I'll wire the money back
to the bank account.

493
00:29:07,496 --> 00:29:09,039
What? Why?

494
00:29:09,122 --> 00:29:10,749
[Dokyung] Because you don't trust me
right now.

495
00:29:12,501 --> 00:29:13,502
So...

496
00:29:14,419 --> 00:29:16,755
I wanna make sure you get your half first.

497
00:29:18,548 --> 00:29:21,009
You wanna break up because you're afraid
I'll take everything.

498
00:29:22,094 --> 00:29:23,095
But...

499
00:29:24,805 --> 00:29:27,391
...now that I have my share,
I know what matters.

500
00:29:28,433 --> 00:29:29,810
I can lose everything else.

501
00:29:30,644 --> 00:29:31,937
But I can't lose you, Heeju.

502
00:29:32,604 --> 00:29:34,106
[exhales]

503
00:29:34,189 --> 00:29:35,315
Come on.

504
00:29:37,192 --> 00:29:39,444
Ah, what's happening here, huh?

505
00:29:40,904 --> 00:29:42,739
[Donggu] Is this the guy getting on
the ferry?

506
00:29:43,782 --> 00:29:44,783
Yeah.

507
00:29:45,784 --> 00:29:46,785
Oh.

508
00:29:47,703 --> 00:29:49,705
Pay up. Money.

509
00:29:49,788 --> 00:29:50,914
- [Donggu] Come on. Money, money.
- Uh...

510
00:29:54,835 --> 00:29:55,836
You can check it.

511
00:29:58,255 --> 00:29:59,256
[zipper unzips]

512
00:30:02,968 --> 00:30:03,969
[exhales]

513
