AUNTIE SUNOK

774
00:45:24,805 --> 00:45:26,015
What? Something wrong?

775
00:45:27,600 --> 00:45:30,269
Aunt Sunok has never called me
on this number.

776
00:45:30,937 --> 00:45:33,105
[vibrating continues]

777
00:45:33,189 --> 00:45:35,983
INCOMING CALL
AUNTIE SUNOK

778
00:45:40,279 --> 00:45:43,866
[Hocheol] <i>Am I speaking</i>
<i>with Ms. Yeo Sunok's guardian?</i>

779
00:45:44,533 --> 00:45:45,534
Who are you?

780
00:45:47,620 --> 00:45:49,163
I'm Yeo Sunok's doctor.

781
00:45:49,413 --> 00:45:50,957
I'm in charge of her care.

782
00:45:51,874 --> 00:45:53,251
[Hocheol] <i>Your mother</i>
<i>is in critical condition.</i>

783
00:45:53,334 --> 00:45:54,877
<i>You need to come</i>
<i>to the hospital right away.</i>

784
00:45:55,920 --> 00:45:58,798
I'm using this phone since we didn't
have your number, Ms. Kim Heeju.

785
00:46:00,299 --> 00:46:02,551
[Hocheol] <i>Oh, my mistake.</i>

786
00:46:02,635 --> 00:46:03,928
Ju Haran.

787
00:46:05,429 --> 00:46:06,472
[phone disconnects]

788
00:46:06,555 --> 00:46:07,682
[exhales]

789
00:46:11,185 --> 00:46:14,188
[car engine revving]

790
00:46:15,982 --> 00:46:17,149
[exhales]

791
00:46:17,525 --> 00:46:19,360
My aunt.
Someone's in her hospital room.

792
00:46:19,694 --> 00:46:20,695
Huh?

793
00:46:21,612 --> 00:46:22,905
[gasps]
[phone chimes]

794
00:46:22,989 --> 00:46:25,783
[phone trilling]

795
00:46:25,866 --> 00:46:27,535
[Nurse B] <i>Saebaek Hospital, oncology ward.</i>

796
00:46:27,952 --> 00:46:29,787
Hi, this is Ms. Yeo Sunok's guardian.

797
00:46:29,870 --> 00:46:31,998
Can--can you send someone
to check on her, please?

798
00:46:32,081 --> 00:46:35,960
It seems someone's--there's--there's
someone strange in her room right now.

799
00:46:36,043 --> 00:46:39,380
[distant sirens blaring]

800
00:46:45,469 --> 00:46:47,013
[tires squeal]

801
00:46:49,765 --> 00:46:53,644
[tires squeak]

802
00:47:02,611 --> 00:47:05,614
[engine rumbling]

803
00:47:27,928 --> 00:47:30,931
[♪ suspenseful music]

804
00:47:46,989 --> 00:47:49,241
[rumbling]

805
00:47:54,538 --> 00:47:55,539
[brakes squeak]

806
00:48:12,640 --> 00:48:14,642
[brakes squeal]

807
00:48:21,273 --> 00:48:22,274
[headlights click]

808
00:48:23,025 --> 00:48:24,026
[sniffs]

809
00:48:41,293 --> 00:48:42,711
[brakes squeak]

810
00:48:44,380 --> 00:48:45,381
[car engine shuts off]

811
00:48:48,884 --> 00:48:50,344
[phone chimes and trills]

812
00:48:50,428 --> 00:48:53,431
[cell phone vibrating]

813
00:48:56,350 --> 00:48:57,351
Hello?

814
00:48:58,102 --> 00:48:59,520
Where are you, Detective Kim?

815
00:49:02,606 --> 00:49:04,358
[Jinman] <i>Uh, I'm at the office right now.</i>

816
00:49:04,733 --> 00:49:06,777
<i>It's a busy night</i>
<i>so I'm doing some overtime.</i>

817
00:49:08,863 --> 00:49:09,864
[Hocheol] Really?

818
00:49:10,614 --> 00:49:14,326
<i>So that gray SUV I see,</i>
<i>that's not your car?</i>

819
00:49:14,952 --> 00:49:17,079
Why'd you ask me
if you knew where I was?

820
00:49:22,209 --> 00:49:23,669
How long have you been following me?

821
00:49:24,211 --> 00:49:25,504
Since the hospital.

822
00:49:26,046 --> 00:49:27,047
Mm.

823
00:49:27,131 --> 00:49:28,883
[lighter clicking]

824
00:49:29,925 --> 00:49:32,344
Tell me. How much do you know, then?

825
00:49:32,970 --> 00:49:33,971
[Hocheol] <i>Ju Haran?</i>

826
00:49:34,847 --> 00:49:37,266
Ju Haran is a person you took care
of long ago.

827
00:49:38,642 --> 00:49:41,061
As soon as I gave you all her information
she went missing.

828
00:49:42,771 --> 00:49:43,856
Hmm.

829
00:49:44,899 --> 00:49:45,983
I remember.

830
00:49:47,693 --> 00:49:48,694
What about...

831
00:49:49,361 --> 00:49:50,362
...Kim Heeju?

832
00:49:56,494 --> 00:49:58,662
[Hocheol] <i>You really know how</i>
<i>to sniff things out.</i>

833
00:49:59,872 --> 00:50:03,042
<i>You're like a fucking dog, Detective Kim.</i>

834
00:50:04,210 --> 00:50:05,211
[lips smack]

835
00:50:05,878 --> 00:50:07,004
What are you talking about?

836
00:50:07,546 --> 00:50:08,547
Huh?

837
00:50:08,881 --> 00:50:10,090
Kim Heeju? Who's that?

838
00:50:11,967 --> 00:50:14,845
Ah. Yeah. Yangpo Airport.

839
00:50:14,929 --> 00:50:16,263
She's on the security team.

840
00:50:16,597 --> 00:50:18,641
Have you told Chairman
Ahn about Kim Heeju?

841
00:50:19,350 --> 00:50:22,269
You're here all by yourself,
so I bet you haven't, right?

842
00:50:24,021 --> 00:50:25,022
[Hocheol] <i>Well, then.</i>

843
00:50:26,649 --> 00:50:27,900
<i>That means we have the same goal.</i>

844
00:50:28,692 --> 00:50:29,985
What the hell are you saying?

845
00:50:30,694 --> 00:50:33,447
I just do what I'm told, Park.
You should already know that.

846
00:50:34,490 --> 00:50:36,784
The Chairman told me to find you
so that's what I'm doing.

847
00:50:37,451 --> 00:50:40,788
Whoever gets to Kim Heeju first gets all
the gold. Right?

848
00:50:41,830 --> 00:50:45,167
And the two of us are the only ones
who know that Kim Heeju has the gold.

849
00:50:45,876 --> 00:50:46,961
[exhales]

850
00:50:47,795 --> 00:50:49,213
Park, listen.

851
00:50:49,672 --> 00:50:52,508
I couldn't care less about who takes
the gold bars.

852
00:50:52,591 --> 00:50:54,260
I really don't give a shit.

853
00:50:54,343 --> 00:50:55,844
So one of us has to fucking die!

854
00:50:55,928 --> 00:50:58,597
[car engine revving]

855
00:50:58,681 --> 00:51:00,641
[crashing]

856
00:51:00,724 --> 00:51:03,644
[tires squealing]

857
00:51:08,607 --> 00:51:10,234
[breathing heavily]

858
00:51:10,317 --> 00:51:13,279
[Hocheol breathing erratically]

859
00:51:23,956 --> 00:51:26,875
[glass clinking]

860
00:51:26,959 --> 00:51:29,962
[engine rumbling]

861
00:51:48,731 --> 00:51:51,734
[distant sirens blaring]

862
00:51:52,985 --> 00:51:55,779
GANGWON SAEBAEK HOSPITAL

863
00:51:55,863 --> 00:51:58,866
[machines beeping]

864
00:52:06,415 --> 00:52:07,708
Geez, what happened to you?

865
00:52:07,791 --> 00:52:11,378
Huh? Oh, you're here.
Help me up. Shit.

866
00:52:11,754 --> 00:52:13,297
[groaning]

867
00:52:13,380 --> 00:52:14,798
Fuck me.

868
00:52:14,882 --> 00:52:17,051
[groaning]

869
00:52:17,676 --> 00:52:19,637
Look at me.
I almost died.

870
00:52:21,055 --> 00:52:22,306
What happened?

871
00:52:23,140 --> 00:52:24,975
Park, that fucking piece of shit,

872
00:52:25,059 --> 00:52:28,395
threatened to kill me and then he just
straight up rammed me with his car.

873
00:52:28,479 --> 00:52:29,647
- [Jinman] Dammit.
- What?

874
00:52:30,564 --> 00:52:32,232
[Jinman] Hey, by the way.

875
00:52:32,816 --> 00:52:34,401
What did you find out?

876
00:52:34,902 --> 00:52:37,363
You're the one who told Park about
the hospital.

877
00:52:37,446 --> 00:52:41,909
Yeah. He said it would settle
my Geumseong debts.

878
00:52:41,992 --> 00:52:43,118
[exhales sharply]

879
00:52:43,827 --> 00:52:44,828
[smacks lips]

880
00:52:50,042 --> 00:52:51,377
[Jinman] Listen.

881
00:52:51,460 --> 00:52:52,836
Once Park finds her...

882
00:52:53,962 --> 00:52:55,714
...Ju Haran is a dead woman.

883
00:52:56,674 --> 00:52:58,801
It doesn't matter if she has
the casket or not.

884
00:52:59,593 --> 00:53:01,720
He's gonna kill her either way.

885
00:53:02,638 --> 00:53:05,265
[Jinman] If you knew about that
and still helped Park find her...

886
00:53:07,101 --> 00:53:08,602
...then you shouldn't be a police officer.

887
00:53:09,895 --> 00:53:11,563
You're just an asshole.

888
00:53:12,064 --> 00:53:13,857
[Jinman] Park has no ties
to Geumseong anymore.

889
00:53:13,941 --> 00:53:15,275
He can't settle your debt.

890
00:53:15,901 --> 00:53:19,238
He's just doing whatever it takes
to find the casket and then get out.

891
00:53:23,992 --> 00:53:26,662
You know he killed Cheon, right?

892
00:53:28,163 --> 00:53:29,248
[Jinman] Chairman Ahn wants Park dead.

893
00:53:29,331 --> 00:53:32,126
And that's why his men are crawling
all over Jeongsan right now.

894
00:53:32,835 --> 00:53:33,836
Did you know that?

895
00:53:35,629 --> 00:53:37,005
I kinda knew, yeah.

896
00:53:37,089 --> 00:53:38,924
And you still said yes?

897
00:53:39,007 --> 00:53:40,134
[Jinman] Huh?

898
00:53:40,217 --> 00:53:42,386
Chairman Ahn is gonna catch Park soon,

899
00:53:42,469 --> 00:53:44,763
and when he does we both know
what's gonna happen.

900
00:53:46,473 --> 00:53:49,101
You think a dead man
can help settle your debt?

901
00:53:50,310 --> 00:53:51,311
[Jinman] How much was it?

902
00:53:52,104 --> 00:53:53,230
Around 100 million won?

903
00:53:54,064 --> 00:53:55,357
If I bring back the gold...

904
00:53:55,983 --> 00:53:57,526
...the Chairman's promised to pay me.

905
00:53:57,609 --> 00:53:59,278
[Jinman] I can settle your debt.

906
00:53:59,778 --> 00:54:00,946
Do you mean that?

907
00:54:01,029 --> 00:54:02,030
Want it in writing?

908
00:54:03,949 --> 00:54:05,325
[exhales]

909
00:54:05,409 --> 00:54:07,619
Wh--What am I supposed to tell Park?

910
00:54:07,703 --> 00:54:11,457
Just tell Park you're still looking
or something, 'kay?

911
00:54:12,040 --> 00:54:14,376
You just need to keep it vague, yeah?

912
00:54:15,252 --> 00:54:17,880
Hold him off until I get the casket back
to Chairman Ahn.

913
00:54:18,672 --> 00:54:21,842
Say whatever you need
to string him along, yeah?

914
00:54:22,134 --> 00:54:23,594
[Jinman] That son of a bitch Park...

915
00:54:24,428 --> 00:54:26,889
...he's definitely gonna die soon, got it?

916
00:54:27,556 --> 00:54:29,099
So you think this through.

917
00:54:29,183 --> 00:54:31,435
[inhales and exhales sharply]

918
00:54:31,518 --> 00:54:32,519
Okay.

919
00:54:32,603 --> 00:54:34,813
[breathing erratically]

920
00:54:41,236 --> 00:54:44,239
[light pained breathing]

921
00:54:54,500 --> 00:54:57,503
You're Yes Money guys, huh?

922
00:54:58,504 --> 00:54:59,505
Why are you here?

923
00:54:59,880 --> 00:55:01,048
[exhales]

924
00:55:01,131 --> 00:55:02,799
Well, it's a hospital, you know?

925
00:55:02,883 --> 00:55:04,593
We're all here to see the doctor.

926
00:55:05,511 --> 00:55:07,137
This is the oncology ward.

927
00:55:08,138 --> 00:55:09,348
You have cancer?

928
00:55:09,431 --> 00:55:10,891
Yeah.

929
00:55:11,934 --> 00:55:14,102
Oh, really? All of them, too?

930
00:55:16,021 --> 00:55:18,524
- Yeah.
- [groans]

931
00:55:19,316 --> 00:55:21,777
Give this message to Ko, 'kay?

932
00:55:22,903 --> 00:55:25,614
You have until the end of the day
to get all of your men outta here.

933
00:55:26,782 --> 00:55:30,619
Or I'll have to take everyone in
for obstruction of business. Got it?

934
00:55:30,702 --> 00:55:32,204
[breathing machine hissing]

935
00:55:32,287 --> 00:55:33,288
[grunts]

936
00:55:34,915 --> 00:55:35,916
Here?

937
00:55:42,839 --> 00:55:45,133
[groaning]

938
00:55:47,636 --> 00:55:49,096
[exhales]

939
00:55:54,268 --> 00:55:55,310
What?

940
00:56:07,823 --> 00:56:09,658
[water splashes]

941
00:56:10,409 --> 00:56:11,827
[Mija] <i>Yeah, I got rid of it.</i>

942
00:56:12,703 --> 00:56:13,912
What about the detective?

943
00:56:13,996 --> 00:56:15,831
[Mija] <i>I told you.</i>
<i>He's not here.</i>

944
00:56:15,914 --> 00:56:17,916
[inhales and exhales sharply]

945
00:56:18,417 --> 00:56:19,835
I'll be there soon, okay?

946
00:56:20,877 --> 00:56:22,170
[Heeju] Can you stay with her?

947
00:56:22,254 --> 00:56:23,964
At least until I get there?

948
00:56:24,047 --> 00:56:25,465
Okay.

949
00:56:26,383 --> 00:56:27,467
[exhales sharply]

950
00:56:27,551 --> 00:56:29,803
Are you really gonna move her
somewhere else?

951
00:56:29,886 --> 00:56:32,848
[Mija] <i>Do we have to?</i>
<i>She's still unconscious.</i>

952
00:56:32,931 --> 00:56:36,435
<i>We got rid of the bug</i>
<i>so why not just keep her here?</i>

953
00:56:36,518 --> 00:56:38,353
<i>Won't the detective find her anyway?</i>

954
00:56:38,437 --> 00:56:39,813
We can talk when I'm there.

955
00:56:39,896 --> 00:56:41,398
[Mija] <i>Fine.</i>

956
00:56:42,524 --> 00:56:43,525
[phone disconnects]

957
00:56:44,401 --> 00:56:47,404
[Woogy grunting]

958
00:56:48,030 --> 00:56:49,031
Hey.

959
00:56:49,573 --> 00:56:51,283
Just go to a doctor.

960
00:56:51,366 --> 00:56:52,492
Why would I do that?

961
00:56:55,454 --> 00:56:57,080
- Just go.
- [Heeju exhales sharply]

962
00:56:58,999 --> 00:57:00,917
[groans]

963
00:57:10,927 --> 00:57:13,221
Excuse me?

964
00:57:13,305 --> 00:57:15,223
Will you call Kim Heeju
and let her know I'm here?

965
00:57:16,516 --> 00:57:18,852
I need to talk to her.
Ask her to call me.

966
00:57:19,770 --> 00:57:22,314
K--Kim Heeju?

967
00:57:22,397 --> 00:57:25,525
I don't know anyone by that name.

968
00:57:26,234 --> 00:57:28,487
I don't have her number, either.
[chuckles]

969
00:57:29,237 --> 00:57:30,447
Mija.

970
00:57:31,490 --> 00:57:32,783
[Jinman] You really don't recognize me?

971
00:57:33,700 --> 00:57:35,535
I was stationed at Jeongsan.

972
00:57:35,619 --> 00:57:37,746
Kim Jinman.
I was a constable then.

973
00:57:40,123 --> 00:57:42,125
[Jinman] Well, it's been 30 years,
I guess.

974
00:57:43,418 --> 00:57:44,544
Don't you remember?

975
00:57:45,420 --> 00:57:47,839
Sunok and I lived together
for around a year.

976
00:57:47,923 --> 00:57:48,924
[Mija] Uh...

977
00:57:50,008 --> 00:57:51,176
[Jinman] You remember me, right?

978
00:57:51,259 --> 00:57:53,845
[chuckles nervously]

979
00:58:01,144 --> 00:58:02,145
[groans]

980
00:58:02,229 --> 00:58:03,271
[phone chimes]

981
00:58:03,772 --> 00:58:06,775
[phone trilling]

982
00:58:07,859 --> 00:58:10,862
[cell phone vibrating]

983
00:58:12,489 --> 00:58:14,449
- Yeah, Aunt Mija?
- [Mija] <i>Heeju.</i>

984
00:58:14,533 --> 00:58:17,285
- <i>Detective Kim is here right now.</i>
- What?

985
00:58:27,754 --> 00:58:29,047
Here you go.

986
00:58:29,131 --> 00:58:30,882
Heeju. There.

987
00:58:34,970 --> 00:58:35,971
[exhales]

988
00:58:39,099 --> 00:58:42,185
[door slides open and closed]

989
00:58:44,062 --> 00:58:45,063
Kim Heeju?

990
00:58:46,481 --> 00:58:48,233
It's Detective Kim Jinman.

991
00:58:49,109 --> 00:58:50,360
[Jinman] <i>All right, then.</i>

992
00:58:51,027 --> 00:58:53,363
<i>You need to listen to me very carefully,</i>
<i>okay?</i>

993
00:58:54,114 --> 00:58:57,075
<i>Obviously, I know you have the casket.</i>
<i>And so does Park.</i>

994
00:58:59,745 --> 00:59:02,622
You need to stay away from the hospital.

995
00:59:03,415 --> 00:59:06,293
[Jinman] I've got everything covered here
so don't worry about that.

996
00:59:08,295 --> 00:59:09,421
Listen, Kim Heeju.

997
00:59:12,048 --> 00:59:13,049
Park and I...

998
00:59:13,925 --> 00:59:17,554
...we're--we're really different, okay?

999
00:59:18,722 --> 00:59:21,516
Park is the kind of person who will stop
at nothing to find you.

1000
00:59:22,350 --> 00:59:24,770
He's so much more evil
than anyone could even imagine.

1001
00:59:24,853 --> 00:59:26,354
I really mean it, Heeju.

1002
00:59:27,355 --> 00:59:29,608
[Jinman] <i>You need to stop wasting time.</i>

1003
00:59:31,067 --> 00:59:33,987
<i>Stop dragging this out and just tell</i>
<i>me where the casket is, Heeju.</i>

1004
00:59:35,280 --> 00:59:38,033
<i>We need to return that thing</i>
<i>to Chairman Ahn.</i>

1005
00:59:38,116 --> 00:59:39,367
<i>Today.</i>

1006
00:59:39,451 --> 00:59:41,244
[Woogy exhales]

1007
00:59:41,328 --> 00:59:44,539
If you don't, Chairman Ahn
and Park Hocheol won't leave you alone.

1008
00:59:45,123 --> 00:59:47,918
I'm telling you they won't ever
stop looking for you.

1009
00:59:48,001 --> 00:59:50,212
[Jinman] <i>Okay? Do you understand?</i>

1010
00:59:56,676 --> 00:59:58,261
[phone disconnects]
[Heeju] Hey.

1011
00:59:58,345 --> 00:59:59,805
[phone disconnects]

1012
01:00:04,476 --> 01:00:05,977
[pained exhale]

1013
01:00:08,647 --> 01:00:11,650
[breathing machine hisses]

1014
01:00:15,403 --> 01:00:16,404
Hey.

1015
01:00:18,657 --> 01:00:19,825
Sunok.

1016
01:00:21,743 --> 01:00:22,869
[Jinman] Yeo Sunok.

1017
01:00:27,415 --> 01:00:29,042
I'll save your daughter, okay?

1018
01:00:34,840 --> 01:00:36,925
[Jinman] So don't worry.
Just rest up.

1019
01:00:37,050 --> 01:00:40,303
[groans]
Shit.

1020
01:00:40,387 --> 01:00:41,388
Heeju.

1021
01:00:44,766 --> 01:00:46,101
Should we do what he says?

1022
01:00:48,562 --> 01:00:50,564
Should we just give
the chairman back his gold?

1023
01:00:51,857 --> 01:00:53,024
[Woogy] He might be right.

1024
01:00:53,984 --> 01:00:55,277
Maybe we should hand it all over.

1025
01:00:55,652 --> 01:00:57,279
Before he finds out it's you.

1026
01:00:58,071 --> 01:00:59,531
[Woogy] I think it'd be better that way.

1027
01:01:02,450 --> 01:01:03,451
Heeju.

1028
01:01:04,369 --> 01:01:05,912
You saw it yesterday.

1029
01:01:07,414 --> 01:01:08,456
If they catch you...

1030
01:01:09,833 --> 01:01:11,751
...the things they do
will be worse than death.

1031
01:01:11,835 --> 01:01:15,046
Even if Detective Kim is really planning
to return the gold to Ahn,

1032
01:01:15,130 --> 01:01:16,381
it's too late now.

1033
01:01:17,173 --> 01:01:18,675
I gave half to Lee Dokyung.

1034
01:01:19,384 --> 01:01:21,052
It's not possible to return it.

1035
01:01:24,264 --> 01:01:26,224
[exhales]

1036
01:01:31,605 --> 01:01:32,606
[clicks tongue]

1037
01:01:42,282 --> 01:01:43,825
And besides.

1038
01:01:46,202 --> 01:01:49,581
Do you really think you can give up
the gold now?

1039
01:01:49,664 --> 01:01:53,209
[Heeju] Just return it and go back
to the way things were before?

1040
01:01:56,212 --> 01:01:59,215
[♪ dramatic music]

1041
01:02:01,134 --> 01:02:02,260
I know I can't.

1042
01:02:04,763 --> 01:02:05,889
[exhales]

1043
01:02:11,144 --> 01:02:14,147
[♪ music continues]

1044
01:02:49,140 --> 01:02:52,143
[♪ dramatic music]

1045
01:02:59,275 --> 01:03:03,905
[Male Singer]<i> ♪ Another day another hour ♪</i>

1046
01:03:03,989 --> 01:03:08,284
<i>♪ Free falling in my mind ♪</i>

1047
01:03:08,368 --> 01:03:15,375
<i>♪ I will find all of the reasons</i>
<i>for leaving ♪</i>

1048
01:03:17,711 --> 01:03:22,799
<i>♪ When everyone around me's changing ♪</i>

1049
01:03:22,882 --> 01:03:27,262
<i>♪ Everyone but me ♪</i>

1050
01:03:27,345 --> 01:03:31,683
<i>♪ All the things I thought I could be ♪</i>

1051
01:03:32,767 --> 01:03:35,228
<i>♪ Are out of reach ♪</i>

1052
01:03:37,147 --> 01:03:41,735
<i>♪ I leave it all behind ♪</i>

1053
01:03:41,818 --> 01:03:45,780
<i>♪ As you fall in line ♪</i>

1054
01:03:45,864 --> 01:03:50,368
<i>♪ I'm not expecting any light</i>
<i>at your door ♪</i>

1055
01:03:50,452 --> 01:03:52,120
<i>♪ There's nothing left ♪</i>

1056
01:03:52,203 --> 01:03:58,460
<i>♪ Just the pieces of everything</i>
<i>we could have been before ♪</i>

1057
01:03:58,543 --> 01:04:02,756
<i>♪ Evermore ♪</i>

1058
01:04:02,839 --> 01:04:08,678
<i>♪ I don't feel it like I used to ♪</i>

1059
01:04:08,762 --> 01:04:11,014
<i>♪ Anymore ♪</i>

1060
01:04:23,651 --> 01:04:28,239
<i>♪ You could find me in the dark ♪</i>

1061
01:04:28,323 --> 01:04:32,535
<i>♪ Still calling through the night ♪</i>

1062
01:04:32,619 --> 01:04:37,499
<i>♪ I leave behind all of the seasons ♪</i>

1063
01:04:37,582 --> 01:04:40,251
<i>♪ I've dreamed of ♪</i>

1064
01:04:42,629 --> 01:04:49,552
<i>♪ But the water's rising over</i>
<i>everything I've known ♪</i>

1065
01:04:49,636 --> 01:04:55,642
<i>♪ Drifting out here all alone ♪</i>

1066
01:04:57,268 --> 01:05:01,356
<i>♪ On your own ♪</i>

1067
01:05:01,439 --> 01:05:05,985
<i>♪ So leave it all behind ♪</i>

1068
01:05:06,069 --> 01:05:10,448
<i>♪ As you fall in line ♪</i>

1069
01:05:10,532 --> 01:05:12,367
<i>♪ I'm not expect... ♪</i>
